Re: "Have you" been to the flower viewing? - - Tense-related
by chikara » Sun 02.27.2011 6:56 pm oldwordstudy wrote:..... The verb is:Ohana mi ni itagootoo ga arimasu ka? ....itagootoo Maybe you mean ittakoto (行ったこと)?itta (行った) - past plain form of iku (行く)koto (こと) - thing/matterarimasu ka - do you have/have youIn English we say "been" for the "thing of gone". Don't complain to me that people kick you when you're down. It's your own fault for lying there
chikara
