Re: "Have you" been to the flower viewing? - - Tense-related
by chikara » Sun 02.27.2011 7:18 pm Hyperworm wrote:The important part to "koto ga arimasu (/aru)?" isn't "have you ~ ?" but "have you ever ~ ?" .....Yes, I didn't highlight that distinction. This page, Ta Form + koto ga aru, from Tim Matheson's Japanese Verbs may help oldwordstudy-san.
Don't complain to me that people kick you when you're down. It's your own fault for lying there
